definition.value: A disaccharide phosphate consisting of a 6-O-phosphono-alpha-D-mannopyranose residue and an alpha-D-mannopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
An acyl monophosphate in which the acyl group specified is acetyl.
An acyl-CoA having acetyl as its S-acetyl component.

A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of an alpha-sialyl residue linked (2->3) to an O-6-sulfated beta-D-galactosyl residue that in turn is linked (1->4) to a D-glucopyranosyl residue at the reducing end. It is found in human and rat milk.
